terms.medium_def:
A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of United Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.2.25; 
only referred to as Bunah (בּוּנָה); 
son of Jerahmeel; 
a brother of Ram, Oren, Ozem, Ahijah and Onam. § a son of Jerahmeel, a Judahite

A location in Judea only mentioned at 1Ch.4.21; 
only referred to as Beth-ashbea (בַּ֫יִת אַשְׁבֵּעַ). §nm
This name is used for a house, habitation

A location near Megiddo only mentioned at 2Ki.9.27; 
only referred to as Beth-haggan (בַּ֫יִת גַּן). §nm
This name is used for a house, habitation

A location first mentioned at Num.32.3; 
referred to as Baal-meon (בַּ֫עַל מְעוֹן), or Beth/-baal-meon (NIV= Beth Baal Meon) (בֵּית בַּ֫עַל מְעוֹן), or Beth-meon (NIV= Beth Meon) (בֵּית מְעוֹן), or Beon (בְּעֹן). §nm
This name mewans house, dwelling
